@wantsui maybe we can add a comment above `max_file_bytes` explaining why we configure `max_file_bytes` and `num_backup = 1` ?

@majorgreys the reason we decided to do this is because if we write to a file we want to cap the max amount of data we can write to disk. if a user forgets that they enabled this and then 50gb of ddtrace debug logs later they run out of disk space, it isn't a great experience for anyone. So we cap the max file size that can happen, and then we _have_ to set a number of backups > 0 (so it can rotate the files when max size is reached), so we decided on 1 just to keep it simple.

Because of that, I am not sure making this configurable makes the most sense. If someone really wants to customize how ddtrace logs are written instead of using this they can just manually configure a log handler for the "ddtrace" logger.

