This case is for relaxed enums that are represented as the union of the primitive type and the enum type.
```json
"oneOf": [
  {
    "type": "string"
  },
  {
    "$ref": "#/types/configstation:index:color"
  }
]
```

 The enum type itself is:
```json
"configstation:index:color": {
  "enum": [
    {"value": "blue"},
    {"value": "red"}
  ],
  "type": "string"
}
```

I chose this pattern as if it's a Union, check if one of the elements is an Enum (this signifies a relaxed enum) and then `t` is the `ElementType` of the `Enum`.

